{{Coord|24|59|37|N|121|18|08|E|display=title}} {{Infobox building |name = Chinese Furniture Museum |native_name = 中國家具博物館 |image = Taoyuan City Government Bureau of Cultural Affairs 1.jpg |opening = |location = [[Taoyuan District]], [[Taoyuan City]], [[Taiwan]] |building_type = [[Museum]] |start_date = |completion_date = December 1992 |cost = |roof = |top_floor = |architectural = |observatory = |floor_count = |floor_area = 900 m<sup>2</sup> |elevator_count = |architect = |structural_engineer = |main_contractor = |management = |owner = |website = |references = }}
The '''Chinese Furniture Museum''' ({{zh|c=中國家具博物館|p=Zhōngguó Jiājù Bówùguǎn}}) or '''China's Furniture Museum'''<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite web|url=http://www.tycg.gov.tw/site/index.aspx?site_id=123&site_content_sn=469 |title=Taoyuan County Government - China's Furniture Museum |publisher=Tycg.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-02-24}}</ref> is a [[museum]] in [[Taoyuan District]], [[Taoyuan City]], [[Taiwan]]. The museum's purpose is to continue and promote the culture of traditional [[Chinese furniture]] and to coordinate with the forest resources of Taoyuan City and the quality traditional furniture craftsmanship of [[Daxi District]].<ref name="autogenerated1"/><ref name="autogenerated1"/>
==History== The idea for the museum was originally established by the suggestion of the Minister of [[Ministry of Culture (Republic of China)|Council for Cultural Affairs]] [[Chen Chi-lu]] after an inspection tour around Taiwan in 1984 to visit all of the cultural centers around the island.<ref name="tyccc.gov.tw">{{cite web|url=http://www.tyccc.gov.tw/englishweb/info7/ch/chinese.asp#01|title=:::The Chinese Furniture Museum-Department of Cultural Affairs,Taoyaun:::|work=tyccc.gov.tw}}</ref>
The construction of the museum started in September 1996 in three phases due to budget considerations. The phase one construction mainly focused on the special exhibitions of traditional Chinese furniture and furniture made in [[Daxi District|Daxi]]. The phase two construction focused on the furniture in early Taiwanese life and the traditional art furniture making. And the phase three construction focused on the peripheral facilities to the museum and space for research. All of the construction works were completed in December 1992.
==Architecture== The museum is located on the basement level inside the Cultural Affairs Bureau of [[Taoyuan City Government]] occupying an area of 900 m<sup>2</sup>.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://superspace.moc.gov.tw/en/local_culture_page.asp?rid=247 |title=文化部-地方文化館 |publisher=Superspace.moc.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-02-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tyccc.gov.tw/englishweb/info7/ch/chinese.asp |title=:::The Chinese Furniture Museum-Cultural Affairs Bureau Taoyuan County Government::: |publisher=Tyccc.gov.tw |date=1996-09-30 |accessdate=2014-02-24}}</ref>
==Exhibitions==
===Exhibition Room I=== Exhibition Room I houses the special exhibitions on traditional Chinese furniture and furniture made in [[Daxi District|Daxi]]. The exhibitions include the terminology, chronicle of the evolution of furniture, furniture in ancient paintings and buildings, revered master craftsmen, characteristics of traditional furniture, the making of furniture, types of traditional Chinese furniture, traditional Taiwanese furniture, special exhibition on traditional furniture from Daxi, prospects and market expansion.
===Exhibition Room II=== Exhibition Room II houses traditional Taiwanese furniture and traditional furniture production techniques. The room is divided into the ''Main Entrance and Courtyard'', the ''Kitchen and Dining Room'', the ''Study and Accounting Office'', the ''Ancestor Worship Room'', the ''Bedroom'', ''Furniture for Reference'' and ''Making of Traditional Furniture''. The peripheral of the museum includes the audio visual showing room, the library, the research area etc.<ref name="tyccc.gov.tw"/>
