An '''electric dragbike''' is an [[Electric motorcycles and scooters|electric motorcycle]] used for [[drag racing]].
Electric dragsters have come of age with new developments in [[Battery (electricity)|battery]] and motor technology. Electric motors powered by lithium cells can deliver power-to-weight ratios similar to high performance [[gasoline engine]]s. Drag races last around ten seconds so battery range is not an issue. A number of electric dragbikes and [[electric dragster|dragsters]] (cars) are competing with [[Top Fuel]] classes. Electric drag racing records are listed at [[NEDRA]].<ref name="nedrarecord">[http://www.nedra.com/record_holders.html Record Holders] ''Nedra''. Retrieved: 17 June 2010.</ref>
==Batteries== Electric dragbike tend to use [[lithium-ion battery|lithium-ion]] or [[Nickel-metal hydride battery|nickel-metal hydride]] cells due to their higher energy density which means they are less bulky to carry. In addition fewer cells are needed compared to a car as the "payload" of bike and rider is lighter. Typical weights: {{Convert|80|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} rider, {{Convert|200|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} bike excluding battery weight.
