{{refimprove |date=February 2012}} 
A '''ladle transfer car''' is a [[material handling]] tool which is used in [[foundries]]. The car carries a metal [[ladle (metallurgy)|ladle]], typically torpedo-shaped (with two pointed ends), from one location to another for processing molten liquid metal.<ref>[http://www.transfer-cart.com] ''special transfer cart on-rail''</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hundred-percent.com.cn/product/454258866-210247392/KPT_50T_ladle_transfer_trailer_for_steel_plant.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-08-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120908021822/http://www.hundred-percent.com.cn/product/454258866-210247392/KPT_50T_ladle_transfer_trailer_for_steel_plant.html |archivedate=2012-09-08 |df= }}''ladle transfer trailer for steel plant''</ref> It can also be called a '''molten steel transporter''' or a '''Tundish transfer car'''.

The ladle is placed on rail trucks but can be removed to pour out the molten liquid.

